        <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
            <head id="a5" altrender="organizational history">ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY </head>
            <p>R.D. Nesmith Co., South Berwick, ME. Woolen mill. Company originally known as Nesmith
                &amp; Tatterson and was a partnership between R.D. Nesmith and John Tatterson.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
            <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
            <p>Includes account book of Nesmith &amp; Tatterson, 1845-1849, listing goods delivered,
                including raw materials and dyestuffs, as well as goods sent elsewhere for
                finishing. Also includes ledger, 1845-1851, of payroll and manufacturing accounts; a
                work and time book, 1845-1848; a weave room time book, 1851-1852, listing workers'
                names; and weaving records, 1849-1850, listing workers' names, number of pieces,
                weight, and number of yards.</p>
        </scopecontent>
        <custodhist encodinganalog="MARC 582">
            <head id="a6" altrender="provenance">PROVENANCE: </head>
            <p>American Textile History Museum Collection, gift of Edward Morrill &amp; Son,
                Inc.</p>
        </custodhist>
